The paper discusses a novel approach for supervised topic modeling that focuses on improving prediction performance while maintaining interpretability. This approach is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the emphasis on prediction performance, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CL and cs.IR.
